datastructures.stacks

Class ArrayStack<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.stacks.ArrayStack<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Stack<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public class ArrayStack<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Stack<T>
    An implementation of a stack ADT which uses an array internally. The ADT is actually dynamic, because we choose to expand the array when the stack reaches capacity.
    Since:
    September 2013
    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
